post_text: Thank you to Chief Richard Calabrese who stopped by each of the five Cinnaminson Schools campuses today to honor the work done by school officials in preparing for re-opening. Chief Calabrese presented administration with commemorative challenge coins on behalf of the @Cinnaminson Township Police Department and the Burlington County Chiefs of Police Association. PIctured here, Cinnaminson High School principal Ryan Gorman, Assistant Principal Jason Meile, Assistant Principal Kaitlin McCann are joined by Chief Calabrese, Lt. Andrew Johnson, Lt. Thomas Lillagore, Jr and Officer Rodger Rogers of the Cinnaminson Township Police Department. #PiratePride #CommunityStrong

post_text: As the rituals of returning to school begin, we always look forward to welcoming back one special group of dedicated employees. Today was the annual orientation for drivers, bus aides, and other transportation employees. This beloved group welcomes our children with a smile in the morning (yes, they will have smiles under those masks) and ensures safe passage to and from school. It was great to welcome them back to campus for an engaging meeting. They are ready to tackle the challenges of 2020-2021! #PiratePride

post_text: All Cinnaminson Township Public Schools will be CLOSED on Tuesday, August 4, 2020 due to the Tropical Storm Warning. The in-person Extended School Year (ESY) program will be canceled as well as all high school athletics. Offices will be closed, but staff will be available, working remotely.
text: All Cinnaminson Township Public Schools will be CLOSED on Tuesday, August 4, 2020 due to the Tropical Storm Warning. The in-person Extended School Year (ESY) program will be canceled as well as all high school athletics. Offices will be closed, but staff will be available, working remotely.

Today was a bittersweet ending to a most atypical school year. Thank you to our students, staff, and families for making the most of remote learning. While we do not know what September will bring, we are committed to remaining in communication with families over the summer. We wish you the very best, especially to the Class of 2020! Have a great summer!

It is the season to recognize ALL of our graduates. As such, we are proud to announce that Frank Goulburn, Director of Curriculum and Instruction recently defended his doctoral dissertation at Seton Hall University (#AllPirates) and was award his doctorate degree.

CONGRATULATIONS DR. FRANK GOULBURN!

The Cinnaminson Township School District is extremely proud of your dedication to continue your education at the highest levels and model lifelong learning for our 2,700 students. #PiratePride #ClassOf2020

Comcast is offerings families a FREE high-speed internet connection during this period of school closure. If Cinnaminson families need support in connecting with Comcast, please email parentaccess@cinnaminson.com.

https://www.internetessentials.com/apply

Additionally, Comcast has made available its XfinityWifi network free of charge as a part of their COVID-19 response plan. Family internet devices as well as any families with school-issued Chomebooks should be able to find extensive coverage of the network throughout Cinnaminson. Again, for assistance in configuring this, please email parentaccess@cinnaminson.com

post_text:
Public schools educate nine of every 10 students. The great equalizer for children, they have lifted generations of people out of poverty and from middle to higher income, helping to set young adults on the path to a fulfilling life.

Public Schools Week honors the 50.8 million students, plus 3.2 million teachers and hundreds of thousands of specialists, administrators, and support staff working in public schools today.

As such, we are proud to recognize #PublicSchoolsWeek here in Cinnaminson. We are proud of our schools, our educators, and all that our students have achieved thanks to public schools. #PiratePride #AllPirates
